         <section id="no-recapture-zone" class="block-section">
           <h1>Post-Litige Clauses</h1>
 
-          <section id="moral-indemnity-structure">
-            <h2>[0] Moral Indemnity Structure™ (MIS) — Strategic Definition</h2>
-
-            <p>
-              The MIS is a pre-contractual protocol designed to compensate for
-              <strong>non-financial damage</strong> (ethical breaches, opacity,
-              symbolic misalignment) that was
-              <strong>absorbed, neutralized, or rendered legible</strong> by the
-              operator.
-            </p>
-
-            <p>
-              This is <strong>not a bonus</strong>, not a retroactive premium,
-              and not a litigation substitute. The MIS is a
-              <em>non-emotional, non-litigious</em> mechanism — priced as an
-              <strong>operational shielding cost</strong> to prevent long-tail
-              disruption.
-            </p>
-
-            <p>
-              It is also designed to
-              <strong>cover the operational setup</strong> of the next phase:
-              including <u>legal structuring</u>, <u>contractual framing</u>,
-              and <strong>the 45-day adaptation window</strong>. This includes
-              legal advisory fees, software, travel, onboarding clarity, and
-              partner alignment.
-            </p>
-
-            <p>
-              It follows a logic of <u>trust restoration</u>,
-              <u>reputational friction compensation</u>, and
-              <u>contractual clarity</u>. It is declared upfront, and integrated
-              as a line item within the realignment process.
-            </p>
-
-            <p>
-              The MIS also serves as a launch fund for assembling a strategic
-              cohort — including former VPs, underused operators, and silent
-              experts — whose task will be to assess and define the operational
-              architecture and monthly value tiers for the 12-month framework
-              contract.
-            </p>
-            <p>
-              These figures, often dismissed or overlooked by their own systems,
-              will help calculate the real cost of integrity, continuity, and
-              scale. This is not retribution. It is structured repair.
-            </p>
-
-            <p>
-              This initial cohort — including two strategically underutilized
-              former VPs and a legal advisor — will be tasked with designing the
-              contractual framework, value tiers, and phase structure of the
-              12-month deployment.
-            </p>
-            <p>
-              Their mandate is temporary: their mission ends at contract
-              stabilization. A separate long-term governance board — composed of
-              a senior legal anchor, a former hospitality executive, a
-              technology strategist, and a fiscal governance expert — is
-              scheduled to be formally convened once alignment is secured.
-            </p>
-
-            <p>
-              The MIS also acknowledges prior damage — including unpaid work,
-              exposure without protection, reputational risk, and months of
-              structural stress endured under unclear roles and violated
-              agreements. This is not forward funding. It is partial
-              compensation for what was already absorbed — silently, and at
-              cost.
-            </p>
-          </section>
-          <hr />
