+        <section id="trigger-clauses">
+          <h1>Trigger Clauses – Irreversible Activation Points</h1>
+
+          <p>
+            These clauses require no external approval and activate
+            automatically when their conditions are met. They belong to the
+            No-Capture Zone™ and enforce structural consequences without
+            recourse.
+          </p>
+
+          <ul>
+            <li>
+              <strong>45-Day Clause</strong><br />
+              Trigger: no payment or formal response within 45 days.<br />
+              Effect: public release of artefacts (Git, multi-level
+              dissemination, press outreach), narrative lock.<br />
+              Recovery: not possible.
+            </li>
+
+            <li>
+              <strong>GP / LP Co-signature Clause</strong><br />
+              Trigger: absence of a strategic sponsor or guarantor within the
+              board or shareholder structure.<br />
+              Effect: automatic disqualification of the deal, framework freeze,
+              suspension of ethical commitments.<br />
+              Recovery: only possible through public repositioning by a GP or
+              LP.
+            </li>
+
+            <li>
+              <strong>Behavioral Traceability Clause</strong><br />
+              Trigger: any attempt to interact informally or contact outside the
+              formal protocol.<br />
+              Effect: activation of the Sovereign Contact Layer™, interaction
+              logging, external posture lock.<br />
+              Recovery: not applicable – such behavior is considered a
+              definitive signal.
+            </li>
+          </ul>
+
+          <p>
+            Each clause functions as an <em>ethical auto-executing switch</em>,
+            ensuring the sovereignty of the framework regardless of silence or
+            avoidance strategies.
+          </p>
+        </section>
